{{main|Chief Inspector Armand Gamache}} == Book Info == '''A Trick of the Light''' is a book written by [[Louise Penny]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=yPar4Uu8szMC&source=gbs_navlinks_s|title=A Trick Of The Light: 7|last=Penny|first=Louise|date=2012-02-02|publisher=Little, Brown Book Group|isbn=9780748120550|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.louisepenny.com/books.htm#ex_atotl|title=Louise Penny Author - Official site|website=www.louisepenny.com|access-date=2017-03-27}}</ref> and published by [[Minotaur Books]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-312-65545-7|title=Fiction Book Review: A Trick of the Light by Louise Penny. Minotaur, $25.99 (352p) ISBN 978-0-312-65545-7|work=PublishersWeekly.com|access-date=2017-03-27|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.buffalolib.org/vufind/Record/1825651|title=Holdings: A trick of the light :|website=www.buffalolib.org|language=en|access-date=2017-03-27}}</ref> (owned by [[St. Martin's Press]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/trick-of-the-light-louise-penny/1101905220|title=A Trick of the Light (Chief Inspector Gamache Series #7)|last=Noble|first=Barnes &|website=Barnes & Noble|language=en|access-date=2017-03-27}}</ref> an imprint of [[Macmillan Publishers]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://us.macmillan.com/atrickofthelight/louisepenny/9781250007346/|title=A Trick of the Light {{!}} Louise Penny {{!}} Macmillan|work=US Macmillan|access-date=2017-03-27|language=en-US}}</ref>) on 30 August 2011, which later went on to win the [[Anthony Award]] for Best Novel in 2012.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bouchercon.com/anthony-awards/winners-and-nominees/|title=Winners and Nominees|date=2015-08-10|work=Bouchercon|access-date=2017-03-27|language=en}}</ref>
