[[File:Veduta della Piazza del Duomo di Livorno - Ciafferi.png|right|thumb|Pietro Ciafferi, ''The Cathedral Square of Livorno'', 1650 approx., private collection]]
'''Pietro Ciafferi''' or '''Ciaffero''', called '''Lo Smargiasso''',<ref>{{cite book | first= Gottardo |last= Garollo | year=1907| title= ''Dizionario biografico universale'' | editor= Ulrico Hoepli| others= | page= 529 | publisher= Editore Libraio della Real Casa, Milan| id= | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Dqc8AQAAIAAJ | authorlink= }}</ref> was born at [[Pisa]] about 1600, and flourished, according to [[Luigi Lanzi|Lanzi]], till at least the year 1654. He belongs to the [[Florentine school]], and painted [[Marine art|marine subjects]] and seaports, which his residence at [[Livorno]] enabled him to study from nature. His pictures are highly finished, and ornamented with small figures correctly drawn. He also painted architectural and perspective views, and sacred subjects. His works are principally at Pisa and Livorno. An 'Ecce Homo' by him is in the [[Palazzo Pitti|Pitti Palace]], Florence.

